Professional dancer-cum-fitness coach Kaffy has shared how she’s been able to stay relevant in her field. Kaffy, who is best known for breaking the Guinness World Record for “Longest Dance Party” at the Nokia Silverbird Danceathon in 2006, in an interview with HipTv said everyone must strive to stay relevant in their field and valuable. According to the 41-year-old mother of two, one’s ability to stay relevant in their trade comes from the hunger they have for that thing and also, the value they possess to impact into others.   I’ll change TikTok game in 2022, says Jenni Frank     Comedian Sydney Talker launches record label     Yung6ix calls out content creators   She said: “Being relevant in anything comes from the hunger you have for that thing. - Advertisement - “I don’t believe I’m done. I’m evolving from one level to another. So, if I still have value in me and people need that value, that keeps me relevant. The celebrity dancer continued: “You must desire to be valuable. You must desire to be a solution provider. What problem are you solving? “So, that is why I remain relevant because I am always looking for something to do for other people, something valuable.”